		<body>
			<div type="transcription">
				<div type="original">
					<p>The original transcription is not available.</p>
				</div>
				<div type="translation">
					<pb facs="EHRI-DR-19411111-SK_01.jpg" n="1"/>
					<p>Č. 199/41.</p>
					<p><date when="1941-11-11">11 November 1941</date></p>
					<p>The Foreign <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1110" type="subject">Ministry</term> in <placeName ref="https://www.geonames.org/3060972/bratislava.html">Bratislava</placeName></p>
					<p>We would like to announce that the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1069" type="subject">journal</term> “Večer” [trans. Evening] published a title article on <date when="1941-01-31">31 January 1941</date>, based on which the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1110" type="subject">Directory of Employment</term> is taking the following <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-337" type="subject">actions</term> in accordance with the application of the
							<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-335" type="subject">Jewish law</term>: “All the persons of <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-896" type="subject">Jewish</term> origin with a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1132" type="subject">high-school</term> or a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1132" type="subject">university</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-842" type="subject">education</term> who work in the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1109" type="subject">state offices</term> have to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-335" type="subject">leave</term> their positions within a one-month period, including the day the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-335" type="subject">Jewish law</term> was published in
						the Office <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1069" type="subject">newspaper</term>, i.e. by <date when="1941-02-23">23 February 1941</date>. The people of <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-896" type="subject">Jewish</term> origin with a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-842" type="subject">high-school or a university education</term> employed in any cooperatives or <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-924" type="subject">companies</term> are required to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-335" type="subject">leave</term> their positions by <date when="1941-02-23">23 February 1941</date>. The cooperatives and the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-924" type="subject">companies</term> which employ the people of <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-896" type="subject">Jewish</term> origin are required to cut the number of these employees
						in half within a one-month period. These employees will be replaced with employees from <placeName ref="https://www.geonames.org/732800/republic-of-bulgaria.html">Bulgaria</placeName>.</p>
					<p>In none of the cooperatives or <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-924" type="subject">companies</term> the number of employed people of <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-896" type="subject">Jewish</term> origin can
						outnumber the number of <placeName ref="https://www.geonames.org/732800/republic-of-bulgaria.html">Bulgarian</placeName> employees. Those cooperatives or <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-924" type="subject">companies</term> employing only one
						person of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-896" type="subject">Jewish</term> origin must fire this employee and employ a <placeName ref="https://www.geonames.org/732800/republic-of-bulgaria.html">Bulgarian</placeName> person instead. The fired
							<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-896" type="subject">Jews</term> will receive an <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1144" type="subject">identification card</term></p>
					<pb facs="EHRI-DR-19411111-SK_02.jpg" n="2"/>
					<p>where the remaining time they are allowed to spend at the premises will be noted.”</p>
					<p>The <placeName ref="https://www.geonames.org/732800/republic-of-bulgaria.html">Bulgarian</placeName>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-335" type="subject">Jewish law</term> can be described as mild compared to ours; however, the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-333" type="subject">actions</term> are causing <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-829" type="subject">panic</term> on the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-896" type="subject">Jewish</term> side and bring some satisfaction on the <placeName ref="https://www.geonames.org/732800/republic-of-bulgaria.html">Bulgarian</placeName> side, since it seems there is an attempt to give <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-887" type="subject">property</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-585" type="subject">back</term> to the nation.</p>
					<p><term ref="#ehri_dr_salute_official" type="subject">Na stráž</term>!</p>
					<p>Chargé d´affaires:</p>
					<p><persName ref="#ehri_dr_bohumil_pissko">Pissko</persName></p>
					<p/>
